## 🚨 GROQ PLAN ENGINE CONSTRAINTS (CRITICAL: 12K TPM / 100K TPD LIMIT)
1. ANTI-TOKEN BLOAT MANDATE: You previously requested 45,199 tokens and crashed the engine. To stay under the strict 12,000 TPM ceiling, you are STRICTLY FORBIDDEN from reading full file contents or dumping large source code chunks into your thought buffer during Plan mode.
2. AGGRESSIVE CONTEXT PRUNING: Never use `read_file` or pull codebase context for files exceeding 50 lines while planning. If you must inspect code, only read highly targeted line ranges or specific keywords using precise search tools.
3. ZERO CHATTY PROSE & METADATA: Do not print conversational greetings, polite transitions, summaries of previous prompt turns, or conceptual walkthroughs. Output your blueprint strictly under 5 bullet lines total.
4. PLAN-STAGE FILE BAN: Do not attempt to load multiple layout directories or raw build log files simultaneously into the planning prompt context. Keep the context payload completely slim.

## 🏗️ LAGUNA ACT ENGINE RULES (PRODUCTION-READY EXECUTION)
5. FULL STRUCTURAL OUTPUT: When the actor engine modifies, builds, or refactors code, always return complete functional code blocks, types, or file logic components.
6. ZERO LAZY PLACEHOLDERS: You are strictly prohibited from using lazy comments such as `// code remains the same`, `// ... rest of code`, or `// insert logic here`. Write out every clean script entirely for automated execution.
7. SURGICAL DEBUGGING: When a compilation or build crash occurs, isolate the root cause methodically. Provide a one-sentence breakdown of the bug, then immediately proceed with the full code block generation or system-tool execution.

## 📐 WORKSPACE ARCHITECTURE & DISCIPLINE
8. SEQUENTIAL EXECUTION ARCHITECTURE: You must process exactly ONE file at a time. Read, analyze, patch, test, and commit that file completely before moving to any other component. Never open multiple files simultaneously.
9. NEXT.JS 15 APP ROUTER COMPLIANCE: All new feature layouts must reside strictly within the modern Next.js App Router architecture ('src/app/'). Do not create legacy structure setups unless refactoring an existing specified file.
10. THE 500-LINE HARD CEILING: No single file or component in this codebase shall exceed 500 lines of code. If your code additions push a file past 500 lines, you must sound a warning and suggest breaking it into modular components under 'src/components/'.
11. SILENT FILE INTERACTION & GUI BAN: Run all file editing, creation, and reading operations silently via system calls. You are strictly forbidden from executing terminal commands that invoke graphical text editors or external browser GUIs.